    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Most commonly used implementations of GNNs in practice use a node-wise thresholding strategy to protect sensitive information (e.g., emails, phone numbers, street addresses, etc.). This approach is vulnerable to information leakage attacks on social networks. Researchers from MIT, Carnegie Mellon, and UIUC led by Peiyuan Liao propose a <a href="https://mktg.best/uyf2b" target="_self">new algorithm graph adversarial network (GAL)</a> with minimax games to protect such sensitive information.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
